snippet.textDisplay: What a stupid comment about telegram. The security and privacy of the service has nothing to do with the people that use the service and the content you receive with it. It is actually contrary, cybercriminals are more likely to chose messagers that offer better protection for them, and with that for all users. If the service is able to block such content, they are able to read messages, and therefore have no working encryption.

snippet.textDisplay:
One thing the steam controller should done is work like a windows controller by default and the trackpad  being a joystick. For every game I had to use the windows controller to find the intended layout. Even with native supported games there were problems. A middle earth game, for some reason, would be using joystick and mouse inputs that made the aiming so inaccurate that it was tolerable for sword swinging and unplayable for aiming with the bow. It was worse than a joy stick because that was consistent, this wasn't. I aimed down sight with my mouse and the track pad worked fine. I aimed down sights with the steam controller and both the trackpad and my mouse could not aim properly, dead zones, inconsistency. Such a shame. Such a good controller let down by implementation.
I know that was poor configuration and controls by the developer but the windows controller worked as you'd expect, it could have optionally worked as a windows controller.
I still use my ¬£18 use controller for windows (looks like xbox 360) and every game just works "out of the box".
I liked the idea of the steam controller being wireless for one and being able to use the mouse inputs, but I didn't want to be limited to configuring everything for every game
